<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF94CE44FF77FF3DD8D33CF0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF94CE44FF77FF3DDA393DC0" blockId="25.[136,778,236,533]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF94CE44FF77FF3DDA513D28" bold="true" box="[136,258,236,262]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF94CE44FE59FF3DDAA73D28" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1920" box="[422,500,236,262]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fractus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF94CE44FE59FF3DDAA73D28" box="[422,500,236,262]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">fractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the following combination of characters: Medium total length; tegulum thin, with proximal third of the embolus narrow and long; embolus with only two keels (PS and PI). Females may be recognized by the single spermathecae, strongly fused to base, with pore distribution widespread by basal membrane.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF94CE44FF42FE2BD8D33CF0" blockId="25.[136,778,236,533]" lastBlockId="25.[810,1451,158,222]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF94CE44FF42FE2BDADD3E3A" bold="true" box="[189,398,506,532]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF94CE44FE65FE2AD9BC3E3B" authority="Mello-Leit" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1920" box="[410,751,507,533]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fractus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF94CE44FE65FE2AD9303E3B" box="[410,611,507,533]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Actinopus fractus</emphasis>
Mello-Leit
</taxonomicName>
„o, 1920; 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF94CE44FC91FF4EDF7D3C96" box="[878,1070,158,185]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obidos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF94CE44FC91FF4EDF7D3C96" box="[878,1070,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Actinopus obidos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A89BC315FF94CE44FBCCFF4EDFD93C97" box="[1075,1162,159,185]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF94CE44FB3FFF4EDEF83C96" box="[1216,1451,158,185]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buritiensis" status="sp. nov.">
